2022 Year in Books

Michael Gillis

Every year I track the books that I read through the website Goodreads. Goodreads is a website that began in 2006, and has since been purchased by Amazon, that allows for a user to select books from their extensive catalog, adding the books to shelves like Read and Want to Read. Users can also rate books using a 5 star rating system.

At the end of every year, Goodreads compiles a Year in Books for each user. It displays different data, such as total pages read, total books read, and average rating. I found myself wishing that Goodreads would provide more in this annual summary, which lead me to realize that all of the data I needed to create my own exists within the Goodreads catlogue already.
